The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Cognizant acquires French firm
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Cognizant acquires French firm
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Calcutta, June 17: Nasdaq-listed Cognizant has acquired Paris-based consulting firm Galileo Performance to expand its testing services in France.        
	The terms of the transaction, however, were not disclosed. The acquisition will enable Cognizant to bring world-class testing services to France, and the addition of French-speaking consultants will help us to better serve our customers in the region, Cognizant CEO Francisco DSouza said in a statement.        
	According to the statement, Galileo helps leading companies in France to optimise and extend business performance through IT system measurement, management and testing.        
	Galileo will expand and complement Cognizants fast-growing global testing practice  currently among the worlds largest with more than 10,000 testing professionals  while strengthening the companys presence in France, it said.         
	Last month, Cognizant had acquired London-based program management consulting firm PIPC Group for an undisclosed sum.                                                                                                                                                                                 
